# Component Library

All shared frontend UI lives in `src/components/ui/`. Follow a **strict re-use or create** policy: never duplicate UI patterns inline when a component exists or should exist.

## Re-use or create (required)

Before adding UI in a page or feature:

1. **Search** `src/components/ui/` for an existing component.
2. **Re-use** it if it fits (extend via props; don't copy markup).
3. **Create** in `src/components/ui/` if missing and the pattern is generic or used in 2+ places.
4. **Keep inline** only for one-off, page-specific layout with no reuse value.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — duplicate status badge markup in a page
<Badge color={statusBadgeColor(device.status)}>{device.status}</Badge>

// ✅ GOOD — re-use shared component
import { StatusBadge } from '../components/ui/StatusBadge';
<StatusBadge status={device.status} />
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — new bordered card + title copied from another page
<div className="rounded-lg border p-4">
  <h2 className="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold">Devices</h2>
  ...
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — extract once, use everywhere
import { SectionCard } from '../components/ui/SectionCard';
<SectionCard title="Devices">...</SectionCard>
```

## Where UI goes

| Location | Purpose | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `src/components/ui/` | Reusable primitives & patterns | `StatusBadge`, `SectionCard`, `EmptyState` |
| `src/components/` | App shell & global layout only | `AppShell.tsx` |
| `src/features/<name>/` | Feature-specific composed UI | `SetupChecklist`, hardware panels |
| `src/pages/` | Route composition — wire hooks, layout | No reusable widgets |

## Component rules

- **One component per file** in `src/components/ui/` (PascalCase filename matching export).
- **Export from** `src/components/ui/index.ts` for public API.
- **shadcn + Glowmint wrappers** — use shadcn/Radix primitives (`button`, `dialog`, etc.) and Glowmint wrappers (`SectionCard`, `GlassSurface`, `StatusBadge`). Pages/features import from `components/ui`, not Radix or shadcn paths directly unless adding a new primitive.
- **Props over variants** — prefer typed props; use Tailwind + shadcn variants consistently with tokens in `src/index.css`.
- **No business logic** — ui components receive data/callbacks; no `invoke()`, no API calls.

## Creating a new ui component

1. Add `src/components/ui/MyComponent.tsx`.
2. Export from `src/components/ui/index.ts`.
3. Replace inline usages in pages/features with the new import.
